---
title: Crispy Chicken & Parsnip Potato Purée Note: Blender Required
description: Everyone at the table will be swooning over this luxurious meal. Break out your blender and whip up a creamy, restaurant-worthy purée of hearty potatoes and earthy-sweet parsnips to serve with crispy, panko-crusted chicken. Pair with lemony apple and spinach salad for an elegant, impressive meal!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6765a7b79bfc6de73c8e1d78-11ece670.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6765a7b79bfc6de73c8e1d78-en-US.pdf
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 990 kcal
  fat: 58 g
  saturated fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 79 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 700 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-chicken-and-parsnip-potato-puree-6765a7b79bfc6de73c8e1d78
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @parsnips{6%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Peel @garlic{3%cloves}. Quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}.

> Larger parsnips may have a woody core. For a smoother puree, we recommend trimming and discarding the core.

Place potatoes, parsnips, and garlic cloves in a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings) with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1/4 cup veggie cooking liquid (1/2 cup for 4), then drain. Return potatoes, parsnips, and garlic to pot. Cover to keep warm.

While veggies cook, in a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place chicken on a #baking sheet{}. Evenly spread tops of chicken with half the @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later). Mound tops with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Bake on middle rack until crust is golden brown and chicken is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a second small bowl, whisk together juice from half the lemon, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

To pot with veggies, add @butter{4%tablespoon}, 2 tablespoon reserved veggie cooking liquid, and 1/4 tsp salt (8 TBSP butter, 4 TBSP reserved veggie cooking liquid, and 1/2 tsp salt for 4 servings). Stir until butter melts.

Transfer veggie mixture to a #food processor{} (or #blender{}); add @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit} and remaining crème fraîche. Pulse, scraping down sides as needed, until mixture is smooth and no large pieces remain, about ~{30%seconds}. Carefully remove blade. Add half the parsley and stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @spinach{2.5%ounce} and apple with as much lemon-Dijon dressing as you like.

Crush @pecans{1/2%ounce} in their bag. Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide potato and parsnip puree between plates. Top puree with chicken. Garnish with remaining parsley. Divide spinach and apple salad between bowls and top with pecans. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.